ited Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"nl":{"1390–1464":"1390–1464","1405–1467":"1405–1467","1420–1475":"1420–1475","1420–1480":"1420–1480","1435–Female":"1435–Overleden","1370–1422":"1370–1422","1367–1404":"1367–1404","Apr 1419":"april 1419","1392":"1404","1370":"1370","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1404":"1404","1435":"1435","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","Abt 1420":"circa 1420","1420":"1420","about 1435":"circa 1435","1464":"1464","1475":"1475","before 1390":"vóór 1390","1405":"1405","Purleigh, Essex, England":"Purleigh, Essex, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Kent, England":"Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, Engeland, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"en":{"1390–1464":"1390–1464","1405–1467":"1405–1467","1420–1475":"1420–1475","1420–1480":"1420–1480","1435–Female":"1435–Deceased","1370–1422":"1370–1422","1367–1404":"1367–1404","Apr 1419":"April 1419","1392":"1404","1370":"1370","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1404":"1404","1435":"1435","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","Abt 1420":"about 1420","1420":"1420","about 1435":"about 1435","1464":"1464","1475":"1475","before 1390":"before 1390","1405":"1405","Purleigh, Essex, England":"Purleigh, Essex, England, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, England, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, England, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Osborne","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Osbern</i>, partly from late Old English <i>Ōsbern</i>, an Anglicized form of Old Norse <i>Ásbiǫrn</i> (from <i>áss</i> ‘god’ + <i>biǫrn</i> ‘bear’), but more usually from Norman use of the cognate ancient Germanic <i>Ōsbern</i>. <i>Osbern</i> was often treated as an alternative form of <i>Osbert</i>. For pet forms see   Hoskin   and   Opie  . The surname has also been established in Ireland (Waterford, Tipperary) since the mid 16th century."],"variants":[{"name":"Osbon","meanings":["English (Sussex): variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbourn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbourne","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Oborne","meanings":["English:","habitational name from Oborne in Dorset. The placename derives from Old English <i>wōh</i> ‘twisted, crooked’ + <i>burna</i> ‘spring, stream’.","possibly from the Middle English personal name <i>Obern</i>, an Anglo-Norman French form of <i>Osbern</i> (see   Osborne  )."]},{"name":"Orsburn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Osbun","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Hoskin","meanings":["English: from the Middle English personal name <i>Osekin</i> with prosthetic <i>H-</i>, a pet form of Anglo-Norman French names beginning with <i>Os-</i> (particularly <i>Osbert</i>, as well as <i>Osbern</i>, and <i>Osmund</i>) + the Flemish diminutive suffix <i>-kin</i>. All three personal names were current in medieval Cornwall or Devon; see   Osborne  ,   Osmond  , and   Opie   (a pet form of <i>Osbert</i>). Old English <i>Ōsbeorn</i>, <i>Ōsbeohrt</i>, and <i>Ōsmund</i> may also have contributed in a minor way to Middle English usage; Middle English   Oswald   is another possible source, but the name was very rare in the late 14th century. For the excrescent initial <i>H-</i>, compare   Herrick  ."]},{"name":"Osborn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Orsborn","meanings":["English: variant of   Osborne  ."]},{"name":"Oborn","meanings":["English (Somerset): habitational name chiefly from Oborne in Dorset, or perhaps occasionally from Howbourne Farm in Hadlow Down, Sussex, Woburn in Bedfordshire, Woburn Park in Surrey, or Wooburn in Buckinghamshire. The placenames derive from Old English <i>wōh</i> ‘twisted, crooked’ + <i>burna</i> ‘spring, stream’, except Wooburn in Buckinghamshire, which is of uncertain etymology.","English (of Norman origin): perhaps from the Middle English personal name <i>Obern</i>, an Anglo-Norman French form of <i>Osbern</i> (see   Osborne  )."]}]},{"name":"William","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Probably the most successful of all the Old French names of Germanic origin that were introduced to England by the Normans. It is derived from Germanic <i>wil</i> ‘will, desire’ + <i>helm</i> ‘helmet, protection’. The fact that it was borne by the Conqueror himself does not seem to have inhibited its favour with the ‘conquered’ population: in the first century after the Conquest it was the commonest male name of all, and not only among the Normans. In the later Middle Ages it was overtaken by   John  , but continued to run second to that name until the 20th century, when the picture became more fragmented."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Kent","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Transferred use of the surname, in origin a local name from the English county. This is probably named with a Celtic word meaning ‘border’. Use as a given name is of recent origin, but it is now quite popular. It may in part be seen as a short form of   Kenton ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Sir William Kent Osborne was born in 1390, in Canterbury, Kent, England, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Thomas Sittingbourne Kent Osbyrn, was 20 and his mother, Lady Joan Algor, was 23. He married Joan Sittingbourne in April 1419, in Kent, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 son and 2 daughters. He died in 1464, in his hometown, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1390–1464":"1390–1464","1405–1467":"1405–1467","1420–1475":"1420–1475","1420–1480":"1420–1480","1435–Female":"1435–Surnud","1370–1422":"1370–1422","1367–1404":"1367–1404","Apr 1419":"aprill 1419","1392":"1404","1370":"1370","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1404":"1404","1435":"1435","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","Abt 1420":"umbes 1420","1420":"1420","about 1435":"umbes 1435","1464":"1464","1475":"1475","before 1390":"enne 1390","1405":"1405","Purleigh, Essex, England":"Purleigh, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Kent, England":"Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1390–1464":"1390–1464","1405–1467":"1405–1467","1420–1475":"1420–1475","1420–1480":"1420–1480","1435–Female":"1435–Kuollut","1370–1422":"1370–1422","1367–1404":"1367–1404","Apr 1419":"huhtikuu 1419","1392":"1404","1370":"1370","1480":"1480","1390":"1390","1404":"1404","1435":"1435","1467":"1467","1422":"1422","1367":"1367","Abt 1420":"noin 1420","1420":"1420","about 1435":"noin 1435","1464":"1464","1475":"1475","before 1390":"ennen vuotta 1390","1405":"1405","Purleigh, Essex, England":"Purleigh, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Kent, England":"Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Essex, England":"Essex, England","Lancashire, England":"Lancashire, England","Cornwall, England":"Cornwall, England","Canterbury, Kent, England":"Canterbury, Kent, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sittingbourne, Kent, England":"Sittingbourne, Kent, Engl